"title": "5734: relationships",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5734: relationships",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God created people to be in relationship with himself and with one another in friendship, marriage, family, society and the church.</p>\n<h2>Human beings are created to be in relationship</h2>\n<h3>With God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:3\">REV 21:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:6-Isa43:7\">ISA 43:6–43:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1\">HOS 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:18</a></p>\n<h3>With one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:18\">GEN 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:4\">PSA 127:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:6\">PRO 17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:17\">PRO 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:24\">PRO 18:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:10\">PRO 27:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:9-Eccl4:12\">ECC 4:9–4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Relationship with God</h2>\n<h3>Is entered by faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:50\">MAT 12:50</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:35\">MRK 3:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:21\">LUK 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:3\">JHN 17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26\">GAL 3:26</a></p>\n<h3>Is expressed through covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:7\">EXO 6:7</a></strong> <em>This is often known as the covenant formula.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:7\">GEN 17:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:14-2Sam7:15\">2SA 7:14–7:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:13-1Chr17:14\">1CH 17:13–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:24\">MRK 14:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:12\">LEV 26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:15-Heb10:18\">HEB 10:15–10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33-Jer31:34\">JER 31:33–31:34</a></p>\n<h2>Relationships between believers</h2>\n<h3>Believers are to be in relationship with one another in the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:28\">GAL 3:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:16\">EPH 2:14–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19\">EPH 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to maintain good relationships</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:3\">EPH 4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:18\">ROM 12:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:19\">ROM 14:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:14\">HEB 12:14</a></p>\n<h3>Believers are to restore broken relationships</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15\">MAT 18:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:23-Matt5:24\">MAT 5:23–5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:26\">EPH 4:26</a></p>",
